# Function: FHIR Error Response Validator
___
### Description
This function provides the capability to assert aspects of the generic FHIR based error response matches expectation.

##### Example FHIR Error Response
```
{
    "issue": [
        {
            "code": "invariant",
            "details": {
                "coding": [
                    {
                        "code": "EXTRA_VALUE",
                        "display": "Extra value - Additional properties are not allowed ('invalidHeader', 'anotherInvalidHeader' were unexpected)",
                        "system": "https://fhir.nhs.uk/R4/CodeSystem/Spine-ErrorOrWarningCode",
                        "version": "1"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "severity": "error"
        }
    ],
    "resourceType": "OperationOutcome"
}
```

### Usage
Use eval to evaluate the function, which is stored as the global variable _errorMessage_
```
eval(pm.globals.get("errorMessage"));
```
Call the various different internal 'methods' to assert against key parts of the error message
```
errorMessage().assertCodeIs("EXTRA_VALUE");
errorMessage().assertDisplayIs("Extra value - Additional properties are not allowed ('invalidHeader', 'anotherInvalidHeader' were unexpected)");
errorMessage().assertSeverityIs("error");
errorMessage().assertSystemIs("https://fhir.nhs.uk/R4/CodeSystem/Spine-ErrorOrWarningCode");
```

### Output
- PASS Returns the code EXTRA_VALUE
- PASS Returns the display message Extra value - Additional properties are not allowed ('invalidHeader', 'anotherInvalidHeader' were unexpected)
- PASS Returns the severity error
- PASS Returns the system message https://fhir.nhs.uk/R4/CodeSystem/Spine-ErrorOrWarningCode

Validates white spaces in postcodes do not affect Searching i.e. you can search for a patient with the;
- postcode DN163BB using both DN163BB and DN16 3BB
- postcode DN16 3BB using both DN16 3BB and DN163BB
